page.title: 02Fish In The River Wylye
page.content: In the River Wylye there are many types of fish,like brown trout, rainbow trout,greyling, pike,rudd,eels,perch and dace. The river is stocked with trout at the beginning of every season,in April.They float a raft down stream putting three or four fish in at a time. In very deep bits they put ten or twelve fish in at a time.Altogether they put six hundred fish in this year.The number put in depends on how many the anglers have caught the year before and how much money the anglers club have.
